  "market_context": "YM daily chart after price expanded above a prior high, leaving an upside fair value gap around 45,600–45,800. The weekly candle was forming with Monday small range and Tuesday a doji taking both sides, setting up a possible consolidation-reversal weekly profile near the 45,835 area.",
  "key_observation": "Monday–Wednesday produced a small consolidation/retracement, Thursday delivered a candle 2 closure into the daily fair value gap, and an hourly change in state of delivery plus SMT divergence on the low confirmed Friday expansion through the range high.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify that price has taken out the prior high and expanded, opening up a new phase of price (reversal, retracement into the gap, or consolidation).",
    "Step 2: Observe Monday forms a small range and Tuesday is a doji taking both sides — no directional information yet.",
    "Step 3: Note Wednesday continues as consolidation, keeping the weekly profile open for a reversal candle on Thursday.",
    "Step 4: On Thursday, recognize price reaching into the daily fair value gap and printing a candle 2 closure, framing the prior days as a large-to-small range retracement.",
    "Step 5: Define the continuation target as the opposite side of the range / range high.",
    "Step 6: Drop down to the 1H chart and confirm an hourly change in state of delivery — closure through the series of candles that made the low.",
    "Step 7: Mark the green continuation zone (around 45,640–45,760) where price should respect; invalidation is a sweep of the low.",
    "Step 8: Price dips slightly lower forming an SMT divergence on the low against ES1!/NQ1!, validating the long continuation.",
    "Step 9: Friday expands aggressively through the range high, completing the weekly candle as Monday–Thursday wick and Friday body."
  ],
  "outcome": "Setup played out as planned — SMT on the low confirmed the reversal and Friday delivered the large expansion through the range high.",
